\pard\plain \ql\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The Profile Widget applies a 20 minute timeout to connected clients. A session that has no activity for longer than this will be considered abandoned. Auth0 will force the user to log in again. The value is configurable.}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0\cf3 Other consumers that use SAML or Oauth2 directly (bypassing the Profile Widget) will have a \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93Session\u8221\'94 expiry of 2 hours or as configured by that application.}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 In addition, the JWT expires after a configured time has elapsed. The expiry time is configured by the client. The suggested time is 2 hours.}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0\cf3 The CustomAuthoriser validates\~the token against Auth0, and this includes checking for expiry.}}